The paper discusses the use of neural networks for clustering, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on deep embeddings and Siamese networks, which are commonly used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper also mentions the clustering of 3D shapes, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of semi-supervised learning and labeled pairs suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the use of losses and constraints in the model suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
